Under the old system of emancipation (p. 137 supr.) if the final manumission of the child was made by the fictitious vendee, the latter technically became patron; hence it was usual for him to agree (con- tracta fiducia) to hold the iura patronatus in trust for the father. By Cod. 8. 49. 6, Justinian enacted that every emancipation under his new form should be taken to be made under such a trust agreement, i.e. should have the same effects, in respect of guardianship and succession (subject to other intermediate changes, see on Tit. 1. ις supr.) as if it had been effected by the old method with an actual fiducia.
